snippet: A pair of bombs struck in quick succession outside a Sunni mosque north of Baghdad on Friday also wounded more than 30 people.
abstract: Pair of bombs strike in quick succession outside Sunni mosque north of Baghdad, killing at least 11 people and wounding more than 30; minutes after attack a bomb explodes near Shiite mosque in western Baghdad, wounding eight.
lead_paragraph: A pair of bombs struck in quick succession outside a Sunni mosque north of Baghdad on Friday also wounded more than 30 people.

headline.main: Iraq: At Least 11 Killed Outside Mosque
headline.print_headline: Iraq: At Least 11 Killed Outside Mosque
